at you have a lot of different sections.  This is good, however the problem lies within the number of members the board has.  It is growing; alas the numbers are very small.<br>
<br>
I have seen this before on other boards where there are a large number of forums to post in, but not enough posters.  It doesn't always work out great.  Users feel lost and it's almost like the members are cut off from one another due to the large number of forums.<br>
<br>
I think it would be in the sites best interest to cut down the number of forums since they are not needed at this time.  There are boards with thousands of members and they have half the amount of sections this board does.<br>
<br>
My suggestion would be to get rid of the German sections, as no one is using them.  I realise that you want to reach out to the German fans as well as other fans from around the world, but I doubt that is going to happen.  I would also remove the fan fiction sections as well as the polls and RPG section.  Those things could all fit into the general or other various sections easily.<br>
<br>
I would have only 1 section for off topic and 1 section for administrative.  You could also fit forum rules into the news section, and pictures could easily fit into the general section.<br>
<br>
Let me say that this place is great.  By no means am I trying to tell anyone how to run their site, I am merely suggesting ways to improve the site as it stands now.  I have experienced these things before and thought I’d share my knowledge.  Please do not feel pressured into do anything of what I have said if you don't feel it's necessary.  All I’m trying to do is help the site out.  This is just my opinion and no one else’s.  All I ask is that you consider what I have said, nothing more.<br>
<br>
Thank you.<br>
<br>
Keep up the great work,<br>
<br>
JP Trudel<br>
